HEADWORD: Saros
<hw>Sa"ros</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/]</ety> <fld>(Astron)</fld> <def>A Chaldean astronomical period or
cycle, the length of which has been variously estimated from 3,600 years
to 3,600 days, or a little short of 10 years.</def> <rj><au>Brande &
C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- A length of time (6535.82 days, or 18 years 11.32 days, assuming
4 leap years in that interval), after which the eclipses of the sun
repeat their pattern, but are shifted 120⟦deg⟧ west.. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sarplar</ent>⟦br⟧
